<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <%- include('head', { title: 'Redacted Bodies | Noir Mak', description: 'Redacted Bodies — a generative art project by Noir Mak exploring queer identity, censorship, surveillance, and digital embodiment through a custom LoRA model trained on FLUX.' }) %>

    <body>

        <%- include('header') %>

        <main>

            <!-- COLLECTION BANNER -->
            <section id="collection-banner">
                <div class="container">
                    <p class="featured-label">Generative Art</p>
                    <h1 class="hero-title">Redacted Bodies</h1>
                    <p class="hero-tagline">A custom-trained LoRA model exploring queer identity, censorship, surveillance, and digital embodiment</p>
                </div>
            </section><!-- END COLLECTION BANNER -->

            <!-- THE MODEL -->
            <section id="collection-process">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="about-card">
                        <p class="featured-label">The Model</p>
                        <h2>NoirmakStyle</h2>
                        <p class="about-text">Redacted Bodies is built around <strong>NoirmakStyle</strong>, a custom LoRA (Low-Rank Adaptation) model trained on top of FLUX and developed in ComfyUI. Rather than hand-drawing or photographing each piece, the imagery emerges from a model fine-tuned on a hand-curated dataset — every image in that dataset chosen deliberately to carry the project's themes of visibility, redaction, and the body under surveillance.</p>
                        <p class="about-text">NoirmakStyle is the same model that drives real-time image generation inside <a href="https://signal-bloom.noirmak.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Signal Bloom</a>, Noir Mak's live-coded, AI-assisted performance system. One trained visual language, two bodies of work — here, redirected through prompt engineering toward censorship, surveillance, and the body reduced to data instead of Signal Bloom's mythology of signal and bloom.</p>
                        <p class="about-text">The dataset design and prompt engineering are as much the artwork as the generated output: what gets shown, what gets withheld, and what the model learns to associate with "redaction" are all authorial choices. The result is a generative pipeline that produces new, unrepeatable variations while staying tethered to a consistent visual and conceptual language.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section><!-- END THE MODEL -->

            <!-- PIPELINE -->
            <section id="collection-pipeline">
                <div class="container">
                    <p class="featured-label text-center">How the Work Is Made</p>
                    <h2 class="section-title text-center">The Pipeline</h2>
                    <div class="row g-4 mt-2">

                        <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 project-card-wrapper" style="--card-delay: 0s">
                            <div class="pipeline-step card-accent-1">
                                <p class="pipeline-step-number">01</p>
                                <h3 class="pipeline-step-title">Dataset Curation</h3>
                                <p class="pipeline-step-text">Every training image was hand-selected and captioned, chosen for how it carried the project's themes: visibility, redaction, the body under surveillance.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 project-card-wrapper" style="--card-delay: 0.08s">
                            <div class="pipeline-step card-accent-2">
                                <p class="pipeline-step-number">02</p>
                                <h3 class="pipeline-step-title">Training</h3>
                                <p class="pipeline-step-text">The curated dataset fine-tuned FLUX via LoRA in ComfyUI, teaching the model a consistent visual vocabulary — chromatic bloom, glitch and datamosh artifacts, signal corruption.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 project-card-wrapper" style="--card-delay: 0.16s">
                            <div class="pipeline-step card-accent-3">
                                <p class="pipeline-step-number">03</p>
                                <h3 class="pipeline-step-title">Prompt Engineering</h3>
                                <p class="pipeline-step-text">The trained model is directed, not simply triggered. Prompt language becomes an authorial act — indexing identity as machine archive, portraits hidden beneath algorithmic masking.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-lg-3 col-md-6 project-card-wrapper" style="--card-delay: 0.24s">
                            <div class="pipeline-step card-accent-4">
                                <p class="pipeline-step-number">04</p>
                                <h3 class="pipeline-step-title">Inference &amp; Curation</h3>
                                <p class="pipeline-step-text">Generation produces variation, not a single fixed image. Selecting what enters the gallery — and what's discarded — is where the artist's hand returns.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </section><!-- END PIPELINE -->

            <!-- ETHICS STATEMENT -->
            <section id="collection-ethics">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="about-card ethics-card">
                        <p class="featured-label">A Note on What You're Seeing</p>
                        <p class="about-text">Every image in the gallery below is a generated output of the trained model — never a photograph, never a training image presented as if it were finished work. Redacted Bodies is a project about consent, representation, and what happens when bodies become datasets; the distinction between training material and generated art isn't incidental to that argument, it's part of it. Nothing shown here depicts a real person.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section><!-- END ETHICS STATEMENT -->

            <!-- GALLERY -->
            <section id="collection-gallery">
                <div class="container">
                    <p class="featured-label text-center">Generated Work</p>
                    <h2 class="section-title text-center">Gallery</h2>
                    <div class="row g-4 mt-2">
                        <% const galleryAccents = ['card-accent-1', 'card-accent-2', 'card-accent-3', 'card-accent-4']; %>
                        <% gallery.forEach((piece, index) => { %>
                        <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 project-card-wrapper" style="--card-delay: <%= index * 0.08 %>s">
                            <div class="project-card gallery-card <%= galleryAccents[index % 4] %>">
                                <img src="/images/<%= piece.image %>" alt="Redacted Bodies — generated piece <%= piece.numeral %>" class="gallery-img" width="512" height="512" loading="lazy" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#galleryLightbox" data-numeral="<%= piece.numeral %>" data-prompt="<%= piece.prompt %>">
                                <p class="gallery-caption">Redacted Bodies — <%= piece.numeral %></p>
                                <p class="gallery-prompt"><%= piece.prompt %></p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <% }) %>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section><!-- END GALLERY -->

            <!-- GALLERY LIGHTBOX -->
            <div class="modal fade" id="galleryLightbox" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="galleryLightboxLabel" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered modal-lg">
                    <div class="modal-content lightbox-content">
                        <div class="modal-header lightbox-header">
                            <h5 class="modal-title" id="galleryLightboxLabel">Redacted Bodies — <span id="lightboxNumeral"></span></h5>
                            <button type="button" class="btn-close btn-close-white" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
                        </div>
                        <div class="modal-body lightbox-body">
                            <img src="/images/placeholder.png" alt="" id="lightboxImage" class="lightbox-img">
                            <p class="lightbox-prompt" id="lightboxPrompt"></p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="modal-footer lightbox-footer">
                            <button type="button" class="lightbox-nav-btn" id="lightboxPrev">&larr; Previous</button>
                            <button type="button" class="lightbox-nav-btn" id="lightboxNext">Next &rarr;</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div><!-- END GALLERY LIGHTBOX -->

        </main><!-- END MAIN -->

        <%- include('footer') %>

        <!-- PAGE-SPECIFIC SCRIPTS -->
        <script src="/js/collection-lightbox.js"></script>

    </body>

</html>
